meanings.definition: To exceed in pulling or drawing out.
meanings.sent1: The little ant outpulls the big beetle when carrying food.
meanings.sent2: She always outpulls her friends in tug-of-war.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outpulls the bird in gathering nuts for the winter.
meanings.sent4: His determination outpulls any obstacle in his way.
meanings.sent5: The tractor outpulls the car when towing heavy loads.

meanings.definition: To surpass in strength or effectiveness.
meanings.sent1: Her homemade remedy outpulls the store-bought medicine.
meanings.sent2: The new vacuum cleaner outpulls the old one in cleaning power.
meanings.sent3: The superhero outpulls the villain with his incredible powers.
meanings.sent4: His strategy outpulls the opponent's every move.
meanings.sent5: The sun outpulls the moon in brightness during the day.
